snippet.title: Pro Tennis Tour 2 | Amiga
snippet.description: Pro Tennis Tour 2 (released as Great Courts 2 in the United States, and Jimmy Connors Great Courts 2 in Europe), is a 1991 video game released by Blue Byte Software for the Commodore Amiga, published by Ubisoft. It is the sequel to Pro Tennis Tour, which was released for the ZX Spectrum in 1989. The game was ported to several systems, including the Atari ST, DOS & IBM Compatible PCs. (Wikipedia)
